x4freetext: Radioactive Ion Beam Facility at Oak Ridge National
Large scattering chamber filled with 4He gas at
pressures of up to 9 Torr. The gas in the chamber
served as a spatially extended target for the
(alpha,p) reaction.The gas pressure at the reaction
target chamber was continuously monitored by using a
MKS absolute capacitance Baratron manometer rated to
and first excited 22Ne states were detected with a
large area annular silicon strip detector array
SIDAR.SIDAR was configured in a dE-E telescope mode
for particle identification with 100 mu-m thick dE
and 1000 mu-m thick E detectors. To block the
majority of elastically scattered alpha particles at
a hollow cylinder was installed at the center of the
The energy of incident proton in extended target was
reconstructed on event by event basis from total
energy of proton identified by E-dE method. Vertex and
scattering angle was deternimed energy of the proton
and conservation of energy and momentum. The excitation
reactions were then calculated by using the yield and
the solid angle covered by SIDAR at each reaction
vertex. Since beam current normalisation was rather
uncertaint, data are given as relative.
